                                         JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Education Department has officially re-opened its online application system for parents of grade 1 and 8 pupils who’ve not yet applied for the 2018 academic year.  Over 200,000 pupils have been placed in schools in the province so far. The department says the system will be open until next Friday (10 November) and it’s warning no new applications will be processed in January.  Spokesperson Steve Mabona said: “The system is running smoothly, and we urge parents who are applying for the first time to make use of this opportunity.”